AUDIO: 'The Seedance 2.0 model is out and now available for everyone globally. One of the more exciting use cases that people may not be taking advantage of is creating engaging opening sequences for your video like this one you\'re watching'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'right now. Welcome back to the channel where I\'m just kidding. Welcome back to the channel where we discuss the creative uses of AI and I have spent hours, that\'s putting it mildly, with the Seedance 2.0 model and it is truly as incredible as everybody says it is. I'

[00:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'have a full deep dive video on using reference images with the Seedance model that we just posted over at the Openart channel and I hope you go check that one out. It\'ll be very helpful to you if you are new to the model. When you combine it with a platform like Openart that'

[00:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'allows you to use reference images so that you can personalize it on every level, it is an unbeatable tool right now in terms of AI video production. However, today I want to talk about a specific use case you may not have thought of and that is to use Seedance 2'

[00:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to create engaging and professional looking opening sequences. Now, I say professional and I know that there are some motion design professionals out there who are going to go "That\'s not fantastic." But for the most part, these things look great uh to me and I think most people would accept'

[01:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'them as professionally done if they saw them in context. So, sometimes when I run across techniques like this, the best way I feel like to show you is my own evolution through it. Now, I use two tools for this. The Openart platform, of course, is where I\'m running the'

[01:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Seedance model with all of its different abilities to use reference images, reference videos, and reference audios and good old ChatGPT. You could use the LLM of your choice to help flesh out these prompts in a much easier way. When I first decided to play with the idea of creating a motion graphic sequence, I'

[01:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'basically dictated my idea for the video right into the prompt box here with the intention of taking this into chat to flesh it out properly. But then once it was in here, I thought, "Well, why not just run it and see what it does." And the topics that I\'m playing with for'

[01:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'these sequences are videos that I may or may not do videos on, but they\'re at least a good test of the concept. So, I start with a dynamic intro screen with motion graphics that read "Text to Speech Wars." The subheading is "Minimax versus Fish Audio." I want the graphics'

[01:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to be thematically appropriate for text to speech, perhaps including a play on the word fish and a visual play on what Minimax might look like. So, this is what it gave us with just that prompt. All right, I thought that was pretty'

[02:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'doggone impressive, but I thought it could be visually more interesting. So, I came to ChatGPT in this case, I said, "Create a good Seedance prompt for" and then exactly what I had typed before and then it gave me this. I\'m not going to'

[02:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'read it all here, but it obviously adds a lot more visual details than I had in my original and should prove to be way more interesting. But, I took it a step further and used Openart\'s ability to add reference images into your video and said to incorporate my logo. I left the'

[02:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'rest of the prompt completely the same. All I said at the beginning was "Incorporating" and then I referenced my logo and this is what we get. &gt;&gt; [music]'

[03:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; Boom, right? That\'s amazing. So, that worked out so well, I thought, "Well, let me throw a different visual style in there." And I threw this picture in'

[03:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'here, which definitely has a specific visual style. The rest of the prompt was exactly the same and here is the result. &gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; I wanted to try the same concept again,'

[03:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'so instead of that weird froggy place, I used my studio. So, exact same instructions to include the logo in there except this time we want the visual style of this and here was our result. So, I thought this was great. It'

[04:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'definitely pulled the blue and purple theme from this and it also pulled the fish logo from the Openart, which I forgot was on the wall and that\'s why that fish showed up there. It was a little bit confusing even though we are using fish. See the irony there? I know'

[04:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'this is a very similar example, but because I did not intend for that Openart logo to be in that original version of the video, I simply redid the prompt with the version of my background that doesn\'t have it and then I got this result.'

[04:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'And by the way, all this more quiet part'

[04:41] [scene:talk]
